y=3D"rich-text" class=3D""><h3 data-identity=3D"headline" class=3D"text-gra=
y-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp600:text-rem32px bp600:leadi=
ng-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words  ">What is blood alcohol conte=
nt (BAC)?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800=
 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">Blood alcohol content (BAC), al=
so known as a blood alcohol level, is the amount of alcohol in your blood.<=
/p><div data-identity=3D"billboard-ad" class=3D"flex bp1100:hidden print:hi=
dden max-w-[400px] min-w-[300px] m-auto items-center justify-center bg-gray=
-300 pt-rem16px pb-[2.25rem] my-rem32px  "><div class=3D"max-w-[300px] mx-a=
uto"><p class=3D"text-gray-800 uppercase text-rem10px leading-rem16px mx-au=
to w-fit">Advertisement</p><div class=3D"flex bp1100:hidden flex-col items-=
center justify-center"><div data-identity=3D"ad-slot" id=3D"billboard_300x2=
50_mobile" class=3D"ad-reset w-[300px] !min-h-[250px] flex bg-gray-300"></d=
iv><div data-identity=3D"ad-policy" class=3D"text-rem13px text-gray-900 pt-=
rem16px max-w-[300px] mx-auto"><p>Cleveland Clinic is a non-profit academic=
 medical center. Advertising on our site helps support our mission. We do n=
ot endorse non-Cleveland Clinic products or services.<!-- --> <a data-ident=
ity=3D"ad-policy-link" href=3D"https://health.clevelandclinic.org/advertisi=
ng" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 transition=
 underline" rel=3D"noreferrer">Policy</a></p></div></div></div></div><p dat=
a-identity=3D"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem=
19px leading-rem34px  ">Alcohol (ethyl alcohol or ethanol) is the intoxicat=
ing ingredient found in beer, wine and liquor. When you drink a beverage th=
at contains alcohol, your <a data-identity=3D"link" href=3D"https://my.clev=
elandclinic.org/health/body/21758-stomach" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"text-=
brandBlue-500 underline underline-offset-[5px] decoration-1 break-words hov=
er:text-blue-800 transition">stomach</a> and small intestines rapidly absor=
b the alcohol and enter it into your bloodstream. Alcohol is a toxin to you=
r body, so your <a data-identity=3D"link" href=3D"https://my.clevelandclini=
c.org/health/articles/21481-liver" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"text-brandBlu=
e-500 underline underline-offset-[5px] decoration-1 break-words hover:text-=
blue-800 transition">liver</a> then metabolizes the alcohol to filter it ou=
t of your blood.</p><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gr=
ay-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">If you=E2=80=99re drinkin=
g faster than your liver can process the alcohol, your BAC increases and yo=
u may feel the effects of drunkenness, also called <a data-identity=3D"link=
" href=3D"https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/intoxication" targ=
et=3D"_blank" class=3D"text-brandBlue-500 underline underline-offset-[5px] =
decoration-1 break-words hover:text-blue-800 transition">intoxication</a>. =
In general, your liver can process about one alcohol-containing drink per h=
our. One drink is typically defined as 12 ounces of beer, 5 ounces of wine =
or 1.5 ounces of liquor. However, different beers and wines can contain dif=
ferent percentages of alcohol.</p><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" cl=
ass=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">The amount =
of alcohol in your blood can vary based on several factors including:</p><u=
l data-identity=3D"unordered-list" class=3D"my-rem16px mx-0 pl-[1.25rem] li=
st-disc marker:text-brandBlue-500 marker:pl-rem24px  "><li class=3D"mb-rem1=
2px pl-rem12px text-gray-800 text-rem19px leading-rem34px ">The amount of a=
lcohol you=E2=80=99re drinking.</li><li class=3D"mb-rem12px pl-rem12px text=
-gray-800 text-rem19px leading-rem34px ">How quickly you=E2=80=99re drinkin=
g.</li><li class=3D"mb-rem12px pl-rem12px text-gray-800 text-rem19px leadin=
g-rem34px ">How much food you ate before drinking.</li><li class=3D"mb-rem1=
2px pl-rem12px text-gray-800 text-rem19px leading-rem34px ">Your age and we=
ight.</li></ul><h3 data-identity=3D"headline" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-b=
old leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp600:text-rem32px bp600:leading-rem38px m=
t-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words  ">What do different blood alcohol levels =
indicate?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800=
 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">Alcohol is a central nervous sy=
stem depressant (it reduces stimulation in your central <a data-identity=3D=
"link" href=3D"https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/articles/21202-nervous=
-system" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"text-brandBlue-500 underline underline-=
offset-[5px] decoration-1 break-words hover:text-blue-800 transition">nervo=
us system</a>) and affects every organ in your body.</p><p data-identity=3D=
"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-=
rem34px  ">Here=E2=80=99s how different percentages of blood alcohol conten=
t (BAC) can affect you physically and mentally:</p><div data-identity=3D"bi=
