6px break-words  ">What is the legal blood alcohol level?</h3><p data-ident=
ity=3D"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px le=
ading-rem34px  ">For most states in the United States, the alcohol limit to=
 legally drive a vehicle for drivers aged 21 or older is currently 0.08% BA=
C. Utah=E2=80=99s legal limit is lower, at 0.05% BAC. Like all laws, these =
legal limits can change.</p></div></div></div><h3 data-identity=3D"headline=
" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp600:text-=
rem32px bp600:leading-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px">A note from Cleveland =
Clinic</h3><div data-identity=3D"rich-text" class=3D""><p data-identity=3D"=
paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-r=
em34px  ">In moderation, alcohol can be OK for people old enough to legally=
 drink. However, if you drink excessive amounts of alcohol in a short amoun=
t of time and/or drink large amounts frequently, your health can be at risk=
. If you=E2=80=99re concerned about your drinking habits, reach out to your=
 healthcare provider or a specialist. Together, you can come up with a plan=
 to improve your habits and health.</p><div data-identity=3D"billboard-ad" =
class=3D"flex bp1100:hidden print:hidden max-w-[400px] min-w-[300px] m-auto=
